<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Boland half year diluted shr up 27 percent.</title>
<headline>Boland half year diluted shr up 27 percent.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1996-10-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half yr ended September 30</p>
<p>		(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr fully diluted (cts)  117.9	   vs 92.7</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		    39.0	    vs 33.0</p>
<p>    Attrib income		38.52	   vs 20.79</p>
<p>    Net interest income	135.27	  vs 102.85</p>
<p>    Other operating income   85.40	   vs 63.36</p>
<p>    Bad/doubtful debt charge 46.25	   vs 24.00</p>
<p>    Pre-tax			38.99	   vs 33.99</p>
<p>    Tax			    5.74	    vs 10.20</p>
<p>Div payable Jan 3</p>
<p>On register Nov 2</p>
<p>Full name: Boland Bank Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said higher fee income and treasury trading profits, plus a successful investment in broker SMK Securities, contributed to the rise in profits. The increase in risk provisions reflected a decision to purge the loan book.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
